'''Christian G. Fritz''' is a legal historian and a [[law professor]] at the [[University of New Mexico School of Law]]  He writes on U.S. constitutional history, and his 2007 book American Sovereigns: the People and America’s Constitutional Tradition Before the Civil War, published by Cambridge University Press, traces the historical roots of [[popular sovereignty]] in U.S. law.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://works.bepress.com|title=Selected Works|accessdate=2008-10-07}}</ref><ref name="lawschool.unm.edu">{{Cite web|url=http://lawschool.unm.edu/faculty/fritz/index.php|title=UNM School of Law ¦ Faculty ¦ Christian G. Fritz ¦ Profile|accessdate=2008-10-07}}</ref>

Fritz received his B.A. degree in 1975 and his Ph.D. in history in 1986 from the [[University of California, Berkeley]] and his J.D. degree in 1978 from the [[University of California, Hastings College of the Law]].<ref name="lawschool.unm.edu" />

